snippet.textDisplay: Hey Tati! I absolutely love you, your videos, your kind heartedness, and the time and efforts you put into every one of your products. I purchased and  received the Tati Beauty pallet back in the middle of December. I was curious to see if the pans are supposed to be glued into the pallet or are they only supposed to be magneticly attached? Because about 2 weeks after using the pallet everyday it accidentally slid off the couch about maybe 1 -1.5 feet off the ground. When it hit the ground every pan fell out, so I had to go to the website to see which order they were supposed to be in.. and while picking them all up off the floor they all survived except Memory Matt unfortunately. So I just wanted to let you know that they fall out of the pallet very easily..  I still absolutely love this pallet and use it everyday! I'll probably end up buying another. Thanks for being such a great person Tati. I hope you and your family have a wonderful year!!

snippet.textDisplay:
So confused about her interpretation of what kind of product Supergoop Shimmer Shade is. It’s not a highlighter or spf for your scalp, it’s an eyeshadow. All the descriptions call it an eyeshadow, because that’s what it is. Many of the articles I read about it also mentioned their Poof Part Powder because they came out at the same time. The Poof Puff Powder is the one you put on your scalp, not the Shimmer Shade. So she must have mixed them up.

It annoys me so much when I see influencers diss a product because they haven’t done their research and have misunderstood what the product is. I thought Tati was someone who at least read product descriptions.

snippet.textDisplay: Angel is my scent. Love it. Wear it all the time. Spicey? Not at all on me. It's very 'spring breeze' on me. Very fresh, floral, fruit, vanilla and caramel. Use just a little. That's what's cool about fragrance though, it smells different on everyone. There was a very popular one once a co-worker used to wear and it made me literally gag. Smelled like vomit to me. She'd be behind me and I'd be talking to someone and look around confused asking why I smelled vomit. Took about two months to figure out it was her-she figured it out-and we were both mortified! Wups. Can't remember the name of it, but it was very big at the time. Never had a problem with anyone else who wore it. It's so important to get the right scent for your own body chemistry apparently. LOL Ciara! That's what it was!
